article.headline: Western Kentucky 72, Montana 46
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. (AP) -- Despite having only six healthy scholarship players, Western Kentucky beat Montana 72-46 on Saturday night at E.A. Diddle Arena. The Hilltoppers (3-0) never trailed and led 37-23 at halftime. Freshman Boris Siakam capped off a 12-0 run at the 2:21 mark in the first half to put Western Kentucky comfortably ahead 37-17. The Grizzlies (0-2) got as close as 14 points with 6:43 left in the second half, but Western Kentucky went on another run to put the game away. Anthony Winchester and Antonio Haynes each had four points as the Hilltoppers scored 13 unanswered points to go up 68-41 with just 2:39 remaining. Winchester finished with a game-high 24 points and 11 rebounds. Matt Dlouhy led Montana with 10 points.
